==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*mixstilaz''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[mistil]] (Dutch [[mistel#Dutch|mistel]]), Old High German [[mistil]] (German [[Mistel]]), Old Norse ''mistil-'' (Swedish [[mistel#Swedish|mistel]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈmɪstel/}}

===Noun===
'''mistel''' ''m'' (''genitive'' '''[[mistles]]''')
# [[mistletoe]]
# [[basil]]

===Descendants===
*English [[mistle]]

